        public static Optional<Prefix> parsePrefix(String name)
        Finds the vendor Prefix at the start of the given string.
        Parameters:
        name - Find the prefix at the start of this string.
        Returns:
        The Prefix, or or an empty Optional if not present.

      • splitPrefix

        public static Prefixes.PrefixPair splitPrefix(String name)
        Splits a string into the vendor Prefix and unprefixed portions.

        If the string does not contain a prefix then the returned Prefixes.PrefixPair will return an empty Optional from the Prefixes.PrefixPair.prefix() method.

        Parameters:
        name - Split this string.
        Returns:
        A new Prefixes.PrefixPair instance, containing the Prefix (if found) and the unprefixed portion.

      • unprefixed

        public static String unprefixed(String name)
        Gets the unprefixed portion of the given name.

        If the name is not prefixed, it will be returned unchanged. If the name is prefixed, the unprefixed part of the name will be returned.

        Parameters:
        name - Find the unprefixed part of this string.
        Returns:
        The unprefixed part of the string, or the string itself if it is not prefixed.
